In short, human evolution has everything to do with solving problems. The more problems you have, the more of your brain you engage on a regular basis.
Whites evolved to live in the cold, like REAL fucking cold no "20 degrees on a winter's night in the jungle" cold. Ice, snow, blizzards, the works. Such weather necessitates the intelligence and creativity to plan out rotating crops, to find out how to preserve and to store...and how to protect your land from neighboring tribes. A constant progression of requiring more and more out of yourself just to keep scraping out a better and better existence.
Africans didn't have to do much of this. They had wide, abundant lands upon which to forage and weather that didn't require them to learn significant advances in food production and storage. They could stay tribal, rarely developing into cities.
You can teach a lot of these things to individuals, sure, but you can't force a thousand years of habit and thought processes into a culture that never needed them. So all that is left is the entire subcontinent being a hodgepodge mix of the knowledge of advanced civilization without skills or the habit to make it better.
